  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: You Walk in the Truth'
      title: You Walk in the Truth
      number: 1
      content: '  The elder [of the church addresses this letter] to the beloved
        and esteemed Gaius, whom I love in truth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Beloved, I pray that in every way you may succeed and prosper and
        be in good health [physically], just as [I know] your soul prospers [spiritually]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For I was greatly pleased when [some of the] brothers came [from
        time to time] and testified to your [faithfulness to the] truth [of the gospel
        message], that is, how you are walking in truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I have no greater joy than this, to hear that my [spiritual] children
        are living [their lives] in the truth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Beloved, you are acting faithfully in what you are providing for
        the brothers, and especially when they are strangers; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and they have testified before the church of your love and friendship.
        You will do well to [assist them and] send them on their way in a manner
        worthy of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For these [traveling missionaries] went out for the sake of the Name
        [of Christ], accepting nothing [in the way of assistance] from the Gentiles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So we ought to support such people [welcoming them as guests and
        providing for them], so that we may be fellow workers for the truth [that
        is, for the gospel message of salvation].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I wrote something to the church; but Diotrephes, who loves to put
        himself first, does not accept what we say and refuses to recognize my authority. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For this reason, if I come, I will call attention to what he is doing,
        unjustly accusing us with wicked words and unjustified charges. And not satisfied
        with this, he refuses to receive the [missionary] brothers himself, and also
        forbids those who want to [welcome them] and puts them out of the church.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Beloved, do not imitate what is evil, but [imitate] what is good.
        The one who practices good [exhibiting godly character, moral courage and
        personal integrity] is of God; the one who practices [or permits or tolerates]
        evil has not seen God [he has no personal experience with Him and does not
        know Him at all]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Demetrius has received a good testimony and commendation from everyone\u2014and
        from the truth [the standard of God\u2019s word] itself; and we add our testimony
        and speak well of him, and you know that our testimony is true.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I had many things [to say when I began] to write to you, but I prefer
        not to put it down with pen (reed) and black (ink); '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'but I hope to see you soon, and we will speak face to face.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Peace be to you. The friends [here] greet you. Greet the friends [personally]
        by name.
      comments: []
